        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Ah yes, indeed `:setglobal` won't work for the case of writing the buffer created on startup to a new file.\n\nTreesitter is enabled by default for markdown files, and `syntax on` enables treesitter early. Enabling treesitter needs to load the buffer, so if you put `set noeol` and `set nofixeol` after `syntax on` you are setting the local values on the loaded buffer.\n\nIf you are editing a filetype that doesn't have treesitter enabled by default, or if you put `syntax on` after the `set noeol` and `set nofixeol`, you are setting these options' local values before loading the buffer, and when the buffer is loaded later their values are overridden.",
