            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "So, I think the only way to for you solve the problem for now is to delete `$VIMRUNTIME/ftplugin/markdown.lua`, so that treesitter isn't enabled for markdown files by default. But if you upgrade Nvim then the file will be back.\n\nOr, just don't use `syntax on` at all in your config. Nvim will do that automatically after loading the config, as long as you don't use `syntax off` explicitly.",
