        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> So, I think the only way to for you solve the problem for now is to delete `$VIMRUNTIME/ftplugin/markdown.lua`, so that treesitter isn't enabled for markdown files by default. But if you upgrade Nvim then the file will be back.\n\nthis only solves the issue for markdown files, and only temporarily, right? also, i'd lose syntax highlighting for markdown, presumably? doesn't seem the best of trade-offs.\n\n\nwhat i ended up doing as a work-around is to move `syntax on` to the end of the file... but:\n\n\n> Or, just don't use `syntax on` at all in your config. Nvim will do that automatically after loading the config, as long as you don't use `syntax off` explicitly.\n\n\nthis ^  is probably the best work-around, i'd say!",
